URL reference: https://medium.com/@divyajoytvirdee/kubernetes-is-it-the-right-fit-for-your-use-case-heres-how-to-decide-caeae550a5fa
DateReviewed: 2024-08-24
Description: An honest assessment of whether Kubernetes is a good fit for your paticular project, from a K8s architect. The author goes through 8 highlighted areas, with at least a couple of sub points each. The areas include app complexity, scalability, team expertise, resource management, ops overhead, cost considerations and deployment frequency to name a few. The author then talks about a handful of specific areas, explaining the benefits or challenges with each. In the end, it depends on a myriad of factors, but the author does a good job of focusing on the high value ones and giving some solid advice.
BottomLine: Good piece which helps to decide if using Kubernetes is the right call
