URL reference: https://www.buildpiper.io/blogs/tackling-kubernetes-security-challenges-head-on/
DateReviewed: 2024-08-25
Description: Security is a challenge with Kubernetes, and many orgs are forced to hold back because they can't solve security problems. Security checks to resolve issues shouldn't be an afterthought, so the author advocates for DevSecOps. This is security during the build, deploy and run phases; but there are still other bits to be considered. We start with a bit of info on pods, but they mention that defaults can be lax and apparently this can be used to "contaminate" other pods. We then talk about runtime issues, but then dip into some survey for reasons, but then come back to restricting traffic through network policies. Then we go through a tour of K8s security best practices. My take is ... whelp. It feels like a bad AI product; it talks a bunch about DevSecOps, but everything feels magic. It's a lot of fluff and basic stuff, and not really a good tackling of anything head-on.
BottomLine: Pass on this Kubernetes security piece that is not head on
