URL reference: https://portworx.com/knowledge-hub/best-practices-for-kubernetes-storage/
DateReviewed: 2024-08-27
Description: Kubernetes storage is complicated, but it is the defacto tool so this article will try to simplify the issues. We start with some of the benefits of K8s storage and where things have to be done right. They have a motivator for why you should use best practices for storage, and then we dive in. They cover dnyamic volumes, scaling, fast performance, security, backup/disaster recovery, and data storage and management. They do a decent dive on each, with a multi-paragraph treatment or more. Finally they have a pitch to use Portworx to handle your stoarge. Overall a decent piece.
BottomLine: Article that talks about many aspects of Kubernetes storage
